This paper is primarily focused on visual object detection, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of deep convolutional neural networks also suggests a potential overlap with artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The proposed benchmark and approach for detecting tiny objects could also be relevant to robotics (cs.RO) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
